data.enText: if a person or an organization holds the copyright on a piece of writing, music, etc., they are the only people who have the legal right to publish, broadcast, perform it etc., and other people must ask their permission to use it or any part of it

data.chText: 谁拥有这首歌曲的版权？
data.enText: Who owns the copyright on this song?

data.chText: 版权在作者去世七十年后期满无效。
data.enText: Copyright expires seventy years after the death of the author.
They were sued for breach/infringement of copyright.

data.chText: 受版权保护的；未经准许不得复制的
data.enText: protected by copyright ; not allowed to be copied without permission
to get the copyright for sth

tr: a document granting exclusive right to publish and sell literary or musical or artistic work
secure a copyright on a written work

value.def: If someone has copyright on a piece of writing or music, it is illegal to reproduce or perform it without their permission.

example.ex: To order a book one first had to get permission from the monastery that held the copyright...
example.tran: 要想订购书，必须先得到持有该书版权的修道院的许可。

example.ex: She threatened legal action against the Sun for breach of copyright.
example.tran: 她威胁说要对《太阳报》侵犯其著作权的行为采取法律措施。
